  "prompt": "What type of grapes are used to make wine?",
  "response": "Wine is made from various types of grapes, broadly categorized into two main types: Vitis vinifera and hybrid grapes. \n\n1. **Vitis vinifera**: This is the most common species used in winemaking and includes well-known varieties such as:\n   - Red wine grapes: Cabernet Sauvignon, Merlot, Pinot Noir, Syrah (Shiraz), Malbec, Zinfandel, and Tempranillo.\n   - White wine grapes: Chardonnay, Sauvignon Blanc, Pinot Grigio (Pinot Gris), Riesling, and Gew\u00fcrztraminer.\n\n2. **Hybrid grapes**: These are created by crossing Vitis vinifera with other grape species to improve certain qualities like disease resistance and climate adaptability. Examples of hybrid grapes include:\n   - Vidal Blanc\n   - Chambourcin\n   - Seyval Blanc\n   - Baco Noir\n\nEach grape variety brings its unique flavor profile, acidity, tannins, and other characteristics to the wine, contributing to the complexity and diversity of wines available worldwide.",
